reviews.text: Great food and good service. This place is packed for a reason. Go with a friend who likes to share and order freely. Everything we had, including the ceviche, was delicious and well worth the price.

Very good food, but the place can really get crowded - particularly on weekends. Service is good and the ambience is pleasant - if not crowded. They make their dishes with careful attention which results in rich nuances in textures and flavors. A real culinary treat!

Sensational food, cool location. Quality of dishes beats 99% of Michelin starred places. Mostly counter seating where you can witness the action up close. Lunch was so good, we went back for dinner the very next day.

Tapas is good! The suckling pig is yum, crispy skin, tender meat and the sauce is perfect!  But am surprised that they ran out of ham!  

Service is average to be honest, we sat at the bar and ordered drink, the staff kept asking us what food we want to order while we are chatting.  The background is a bit noisy.
It's definitely on the pricey side, but well worth it. Be sure to order the scallop ceviche.
